Putin’s Deputy Kozak May Govern St. Petersburg, Kommersant Says

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-08-11T03:59:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/putin-s-deputy-kozak-may-govern-st-petersburg-kommersant-says.html
Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Kozak,
who has known Russian Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  since the
early 1990s, may become the new governor of  St. Petersburg ,
replacing Valentina Matvienko,  Kommersant  reported, citing
people it didn’t name.  Kozak has been in charge of regional development and
subsequently plans for the 2014 Sochi Olympics in Putin’s
government.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  